    "created_at": "2022-02-08T17:08:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2022-02-08T17:08:06Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think reverting on decoding failure if there is no fallback catch clause would actually be consistent with the current implementation.\r\n\r\nMaybe we could change that behaviour for 0.9.0? The property \"if execution ends up inside a catch block, then the call must have failed\" is something I would not want to change, but reverting on error decoding failure is actually not too bad. It would even be consistent with reverting on return data decoding failure.",
